<p>I'm using Entity Framework. </p>  <p>According to this: <a href="https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/data/gg193959.aspx" rel="nofollow">https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/data/gg193959.aspx</a></p>  <blockquote>   <p>"With no additional code or markup changes in the application, an   existing MVC application will perform client side validation"</p> </blockquote>  <p>The binding is correct.</p>  <p>The validation doesn't filter down to the DataGrid and I get an exception on SaveChanges.</p>  <p><strong>Model</strong></p>  <pre><code>private string _Sponsor; [Required] [StringLength(20, MinimumLength = 3)] public string Sponsor {     get     {         return _Sponsor;     }     set     {         _Sponsor = value;         NotifyPropertyChanged("Sponsor");     } } </code></pre>  <p><strong>MainWindow.xaml.cs</strong></p>  <pre><code>JobCollectionContext _context = new JobCollectionContext();  CollectionViewSource jobViewSource = ((CollectionViewSource)(this.FindResource("jobViewSource")));  _context.JobCollection.Load();  jobViewSource.Source = _context.JobCollection.Local; </code></pre>  <p><strong>MainWindow.xaml</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;DataGridTextColumn Header="Sponsor" Binding="{Binding Sponsor, UpdateSourceTrigger=LostFocus, Mode=TwoWay, NotifyOnValidationError=true, ValidatesOnExceptions=true}" /&gt; </code></pre>